a doll 's house is a 1973 franco-british drama film directed by joseph losey , based on the play of the same name by henrik ibsen . it stars jane fonda in the role of nora helmer and david warner as her domineering husband , torvald . in the united states , the film was broadcast nationally on the abc television network . losey 's version of the classic play was extensively adapted for film . from ibsen 's expository dialogue , entire new scenes were developed by playwright david mercer and integrated through a variety of invented sets . losey 's alterations generated considerable controversy , as did his casting of outspoken actress fonda – known at the time as " hanoi jane " – in the lead role .